    {
        "id": "2488222afe37a0d1",
        "type": "join",
        "z": "a9a6010b932de479",
        "name": "Agg. Effort",
        "mode": "reduce",
        "build": "object",
        "property": "payload",
        "propertyType": "msg",
        "key": "topic",
        "joiner": "\\n",
        "joinerType": "str",
        "useparts": false,
        "accumulate": true,
        "timeout": "",
        "count": "",
        "reduceRight": false,
        "reduceExp": "(\t\t$scope  := payload.scope;\t\t$match  := $lookup($A, $scope);\t\t$effort := $number(payload.effort_pct);\t\t\t\t$merge([\t\t\t$A,\t\t\t{ $scope: $exists($match) ?\t\t\t\t{ \"t\": $match.t + $effort, \"c\": $match.c + 1 } :\t\t\t\t{ \"t\": $effort, \"c\": 1 }\t\t\t}\t\t])\t)",
        "reduceInit": "{}",
        "reduceInitType": "json",
        "reduceFixup": "$each($A, function($v, $k) {\t    { \"scope\": $k, \"effort\": $v.t / $v.c }\t})",
        "x": 670,
        "y": 340,
        "wires": [
            [
                "e2a9fa8fa8092b9c"
            ]
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "a485a10b6b176e73",
        "type": "comment",
        "z": "a9a6010b932de479",
        "name": "CSV: Input schema",
        "info": "## Format\n\nPipe (` | `) separated CSV with the following 12 columns:\n\n| # | Column Name       | Description                                      |\n|---|-------------------|--------------------------------------------------|\n| 1 | `session_id`      | UUID v7 identifying the session                  |\n| 2 | `friction_category` | One of `Context Fragmentation`, `State Brittleness`, `Missing Guardrails` |\n| 3 | `scope`           | Business domain or logical module (e.g. `Checkout`, `Checkout(tests)`) |\n| 4 | `effort_pct`      | Relative cognitive effort as an integer percentage |\n| 5 | `diagnosis`       | Free-text diagnosis sentence                     |\n| 6 | `tokens_in`       | Input tokens consumed in the session             |\n| 7 | `tokens_out`      | Output tokens consumed in the session            |\n| 8 | `tokens_total`    | Total tokens (input + output)                    |\n| 9 | `cost_total`      | Total cost in USD                                |\n| 10 | `model_provider`  | Provider name (e.g. `deepseek`, `anthropic`)     |\n| 11 | `model_id`        | Model identifier (e.g. `deepseek-v4-flash`)      |\n| 12 | `timestamp`       | ISO 8601 datetime with millisecond precision and `Z` suffix |\n\n## Example row\n\n```\n019e9abb-58e8-76fe-adea-b47a634e8881 | Context Fragmentation | Checkout | 85 | Building a complete picture of the checkout handler required reading 10 files across 5 directories | 30226 | 2476 | 152638 | 0.0052607408 | deepseek | deepseek-v4-flash | 2026-06-06T02:20:29.800Z\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- Column names are **lowercase snake_case** throughout.\n- The `scope` column uses a capitalized business domain name, optionally with a parenthetical sub-scope (e.g. `Checkout(tests)`, `Checkout(db)`). No file paths or globs.\n- The `effort_pct` values across rows from the same feedback loop must sum to exactly 100.\n- The first line of the file is a header row matching the column names above.\n",
        "x": 300,
        "y": 220,
        "wires": []
    },
